PLUGKIT FIXES + DIAGNOSES (2026-06 /gm-skill, multi-issue). (1) WASM STATE-READ OVERFLOW (diagen 'Start offset -2GB outside buffer' bricking any state-reading verb, surviving reboots): ROOT = two UNGUARDED wasm-result decode paths in plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js -- the watcher dispatch (new Uint8Array(memory.buffer, ptr, len) at ~3112) and the CLI dispatch (~3822) decoded the i64-packed (ptr|len<<32) result WITHOUT guardWasmRange (only the main dispatch_verb path at :180 was guarded). On large state the wasm hands back an overflowed ptr/len and V8's Uint8Array throws the raw '-2GB' error, crashing the watcher loop. FIX: added guardWasmRange before both -> the watcher try/catch (:3170) writes {ok:false,error:'wasm-memory-read-out-of-bounds'} instead of bricking; orchestrator survives, reboots no longer re-brick. Ships via cascade wrapper-refresh (JS, no wasm rebuild). DEEP growth-cap (why state crosses 2GB) needs a multi-GB repro = follow-up; state.rs is a small next-step file, no text journal. (2) SCREENSHOT CHECKING: page.screenshot() returns a real PNG Buffer (witnessed 19628 bytes magic 89504e47) but returning it INLINE stringifies to useless bytes. FIX/recipe (witnessed live, image rendered): page.screenshot({path:'<abs>.png'}) then Read the path -- the Read tool renders the PNG. Documented in browser.md + synced browser.rs. (3) TERRAIN false-completion: NOT a gate bug -- c:/dev/terrain/.gm/prd.yml shows do-rows and revert-rows (do X, then 'we incorrectly wrote X, revert', then redo) all status:completed with NARRATIVE witnesses ('diff -> exit 0' not captured exec). Mechanism = self-cancelling re-plans + unverified witnesses; the gate honestly sees all-rows-done while the deliverable oscillates. Durable fix is anti-thrash + witness-realness = instructional follow-up. (4) NOTICING: watcher died right after a browser screenshot dispatch (233 ok -> 234-238 unconsumed, ts 114s stale, supervisor didn't respawn in 114s); booted to recover -- browser-dispatch-vs-watcher-death / supervisor-respawn-timing follow-up. LESSON: EVERY new Uint8Array(memory.buffer, ptr, len) on a wasm-RETURNED ptr/len must go through guardWasmRange; input-write .set() paths (alloc'd ptr + agent-bounded length) are safe.